Description

something used for making mathematical calculations, 
in particular a small electronic device with a keyboard and a visual display.
An electronic calculator is typically a portable electronic device used to perform calculations, ranging from basic arithmetic to complex mathematics. 
The first solid-state electronic calculator was created in the early 1960s.


A calculator is a device that performs arithmetic operations on numbers.


The simplest calculators can do only addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division.
